From Edmund West Subject AVS presentation University of Toronto Instructional and Research Computing is sponsoring a technical presentation on Visualization Software A d v a n c e d V i s u a l S y s t e m s A V S S o f t w a r e PM PM Thursday May Sandford Fleming Building Room Advanced Visual Systems will present this technical seminar on AVS the world's leading visualization software AVS is a point and click module driven easy to use product that produces full color two or three dimensional rendered scenes for interactive It is supported on all current Unix RISC platforms from Sun SGI IBM H P DG and It also runs under DEC AVS is in its fourth year on the street and is very All fields of science engineering medicine and even business applications now use This seminar will focus on its many features in technical detail during a half hour slide Following a question period there will be a live demonstration using a Sun In addition a new AVS program called CAMPUS will be introduced at this Also discussed will be the International AVS Center which provides an on line repository of over graphics modules at the North Carolina Supercomputer Center in Raliegh AVS has imbedded tools to write one's own customized modules should these not be available with AVS or from AVS S p e a k e r s The scheduled speaker for this presentation is Paul Ecklund of Ecklund Associates the distributor of AVS in T h i s p r e s e n t a t i o n i s o p e n t o t h e p u b l i c